article.headline: W. Kentucky 92, Troy 57
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Tyrone Brazelton scored 15 points and Western Kentucky built as much as a 48-point lead in routing Troy 92-57 Wednesday night. The Hilltoppers (20-5, 12-1 Sun Belt) extended their winning streak to 10 games, placing five players in double figures in the one-sided game. Troy (10-15, 3-11) never led and trailed 88-40 after a basket by Steffphon Pettigrew with 4:54 to play. Ty Rogers, A.J. Slaughter and Boris Siakam scored 12 points each for Western Kentucky. Siakam had a perfect night, with 5-of-5 shooting from the floor and making both of his free throws. Courtney Lee, Western Kentucky's leading scorer at 21.6 points per game, finished with 10. Jerome Odem led the Trojans with 18 points.
